# .adlc/ evidence is the durable record and is TRACKED BY DEFAULT — only known-scratch paths are
# ignored. tickets.json is the contract every gate reads, manifest.jsonl the hash-chained gate
# evidence P6 surfaces, findings.jsonl P7's only input. This was an allowlist (`.adlc/*` plus
# negations) until a prosecutor pass pointed out the obvious: under an allowlist, any NEW evidence
# file a future adlc version writes — an acceptance record, a rails lockfile — is silently untracked
# on creation, with no error and nothing in the diff to notice. That is the same
# machinery-switched-off shape that hid the stale plugin and the untracked ledger. Deny the scratch,
# keep the evidence.
.adlc/tmp/
.adlc/cache/
.claude/settings.local.json
